# Implementation Plan - Unify Currency Presentation

## Goal Description
Unify the presentation of monetary values across the application (Dashboard and Report Tables). Positive values should be green, and negative values should be red.

## Proposed Changes

### Frontend
#### [MODIFY] [App.css](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/Facturas/frontend/src/App.css)
- Add utility classes for currency colors:
    - `.text-currency-positive` (Green)
    - `.text-currency-negative` (Red)

#### [MODIFY] [StatCard.tsx](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/Facturas/frontend/src/components/molecules/StatCard/StatCard.tsx)
- Inspect the `value` prop.
- If `value` represents a negative number (contains `-`), apply `.text-currency-negative`.
- If `value` represents a positive number (and is not zero), apply `.text-currency-positive`.

#### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/Facturas/frontend/src/App.tsx)
- In the Report Table rendering logic:
    - Apply the same logic to the cells modifying `subtotal`, `iva`, `total`, `descuentos`.
    - Create a small helper function `getCurrencyClass` inside [App.tsx](file:///f:/1.%20Cloud/4.%20AI/1.%20Antigravity/Facturas/frontend/src/App.tsx) or inline logic.

